# Web Development

Apply only to web application tasks.

## Core Principles

- Follow the framework and architecture already selected by the project.
- Prefer clear, typed, composable code.
- Keep business rules independent from presentation and transport when practical.
- Validate all external input.
- Design explicit loading, error, empty, and offline behavior where relevant.
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies and abstractions.

## Security

- Escape or sanitize untrusted content according to rendering context.
- Enforce authentication and authorization on trusted systems.
- Use secure transport and approved cookie/token practices.
- Keep secrets out of browser bundles.
- Validate uploads by type, size, and authorization.
- Apply appropriate security headers at the hosting layer.

## Performance

- Measure before optimizing.
- Split large optional features.
- Avoid request waterfalls.
- Paginate or virtualize large collections.
- Optimize media and reserve layout space.

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML.
- Support keyboard navigation.
- Preserve readable contrast and focus visibility.
- Provide text alternatives and accessible names.

## Testing

- Unit test pure logic.
- Integration test important module boundaries.
- End-to-end test critical user workflows.
- Include accessibility and responsive checks when user-facing behavior changes.
